    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Hungarian Chamber to Miklós Oláh (Bratislava, 26 March
                    1549)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. Oláh encourages them to take care of the Eger
                            soldiers’ payment. He knows that they always gladly do what he asks, but
                            this is not their competence but that of the purser, who told him he was
                            taking care of it and has even travelled there. As for the royal order
                            on the benefices, they have not received it yet, but they are expecting
                            it every hour. 2. They recommend that Oláh take on the title of supremus
                            comes, and that Ostrosith oversee the county in his name. He should ask
                            for the letter of accreditation to be changed, and an order should be
                            made out at the German chancellery for Christoph Görtschacher, the
                            captain of the castle, to hand over the administration of the estate to
                            Ostrosith. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad dominum cancellarium.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Reverendissime Domine, Domine Observandissime, salutem et
                    servitiorum nostrorum commendationem!</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[1.] Hortatur<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">See Ep.
                            714.<ref>olahus.tei.15490317_1</ref></note> nos Reverendissima Dominatio
                    Vestra, ut solutionem gentium <placeName>Agriae</placeName> existentium curemus.
                    Sciat nos, quaecumque viribus nostris convenientia sunt, ex animo <del
                        corresp="author">in favore velle et libenter facere paratos</del><add
                        corresp="author" type="corr">facturos</add> causa Reverendissimae
                    Dominationis Vestrae, cui inservire parati simus, verum omnis <add
                        corresp="author" type="insert">cura</add> solutionis militum sive equituum
                    sive peditum, domino magistro<note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Probably Hans
                        Holtzer, Court Paymaster or Mangus Scheitz, Army Paymaster, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Kenyeres</hi> 2005, 256; and <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Kenyeres</hi> 2007.</note> solutionis regiae maiestatis incumbit, cum
                    quo proximis diebus contulimus, significavitque se Agriensium curam habiturum,
                    quo etiam profectus est, nec deest illi, ut intelligimus, pecunia, et nos
                    quicquid usquam ex contributione colligi potest, commisimus manibus illius
                    assignari.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Ceterum, quod pro certeo possumus scribere, hucusque deliberatio
                    maiestatis regiae super solutione salariorum ad nos perlata non est, nec interim
                    cuiquam respondere licet exspectamus omnibus horis, ut iam tandem dirigat huc
                    sua maiestas eam ipsam deliberationem descriptam.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">[2.] <del corresp="author">Iussit</del> Praeterea <del
                        corresp="author">quod</del> iussit <persName>maiestas regia</persName>
                    tractari cum <persName>Ioanne Ostrosith</persName>,<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.3">János Ostrosith or Ostrošić was Provisor of Jajce in 1526.
                        In 1549, he became Provisor of the castle of Trenčín and <hi rend="italic"
                            >ispán</hi> of Trencsén county. See <hi rend="smallcap">C.
                            Tóth–Horváth–Neumann–Pálosfalvi</hi> 2017, I, 143; and <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Kenyeres</hi> 1997, 110–114. To the case, see MNL OL, E
                        21, 1549.03.24.a and 1549.03.27.</note> ut <del corresp="author">per
                        nos</del> expeditus capessat officium comitatus Trinchinensis ei
                    administratoris proventuum illius arcis. Accepit quidem ille binas litteras
                    maiestatis regiae ostenditque eas reverendissimo domino locumtenenti<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.4">Pál Várday.</note> et consiliariis, et iudicat
                    illis se nihil effecturum, dicit enim promissum sibi esse comitatus honorem
                    durante bene placito <add corresp="author" type="insert">regio</add> verum
                        <milestone unit="pb"/>illis verbis functionem vice nostri honoris comitatus
                    eiusdem. Item praefatum Ioannem vice et in persona nostra regia, loco comitis
                    vestri etc. Arbitratur eo tendere, ut ipse sit futurus vicecomes.<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.5">On how Trencsén county functioned, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">C. Tóth–Horváth–Neumann–Pálosfalvi</hi> 2017, II,
                        282–287.</note> Addit commissionem directam esse ad vicecomitem <del
                        corresp="author">et iudices</del> (quem nullum esse nunc dicit) et iudices
                    ac universitatem nobilium, quos credit non refragaturos, verum ceteri comitatus
                    vestri <del corresp="author">magnifici et ecclesistici alii</del><add
                        corresp="author" type="corr">reverendissimi, reverendi, magnifici etc.</add>
                    non essent litteras curaturi, quando non essent ad eos directae. Supplicat
                    igitur pro reformatione litterarum, et nos rogamus, iubeat ita describi
                    litteras, ne cui difficultati daretur occasio, sed necesse est, ut ex
                    cancellaria Germanica expediatur mandatum ad dominum <persName>Christoferum
                        Gertsharher</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.6">Christoph
                        Görtschacher was Captain of the castle of Trenčín, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Kenyeres</hi> 1997, 103.</note> praefectum arcis, ut admittat hunc
                        <persName>Ostrosith</persName> ad bonorum administrationem <del
                        corresp="author">tam in</del> et curam tam in arce, quam possessionibus
                    alioqui nunquam ille admittet <del corresp="author">istum</del> forte et aliis
                    esset opus litteris ad civitatem et iudices ac colonos bonorum arcis, ut eum pro
                    administratore proventuum arcis recognoscant etc. Nos hac de re nihil ad
                    maiestatem regiam scripsimus, sed iam tamen paucis rogavimus <add
                        corresp="author" type="insert">dominos</add> consiliarios <del
                        corresp="author">aulicos</del><add corresp="author" type="corr"
                        >aulicae</add> Camerae, ut iubeat expediri litteras ad Ghertsharher.
                    Dominationem Vestram Reverendissimam Deus servet feliciter.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.6"><placeName>Posonii</placeName> die 26. Martii 1549.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.7">Sacrae.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.7">I.e. sacrae regiae
                        maiestatis consiliarii.</note>.</p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>Probably on the outer side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.8"> Reverendissimo domino Nicolao Olaho episcopo ecclesiae Agriensis,
                    cancellario regiae maiestatis Romanorum, Hungariae etc. dignissimo domino
                    observandissimo.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
